ong second vault helped him fly into first with a score of 14.949.\", \"from\": 449, \"to\": 619, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the competition\", \"from\": 483, \"to\": 498}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic debut\", \"from\": 502, \"to\": 515}, {\"ngram\": \"a brilliant start\", \"from\": 526, \"to\": 543}, {\"ngram\": \"a strong second vault\", \"from\": 548, \"to\": 569}, {\"ngram\": \"a score\", \"from\": 601, \"to\": 608}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He finished behind Carlos Edriel Yulo of thePhilippines, who claimed gold, and Armenia's Artur Davtyan, who took silver.\", \"from\": 621, \"to\": 741, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 640, \"end\": 658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Yulo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carlos Edriel Yulo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Yulo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Yulo\"}, {\"begin\": 700, \"end\": 707, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Armenia\", \"score\": 0.890440545589563, \"rank\": 0.12303154381385335, \"text\": \"Armenia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Armenia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Armenia\"}, {\"begin\": 710, \"end\": 723, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artur_Davtyan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Artur Davtyan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artur_Davtyan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artur_Davtyan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 690, \"to\": 694}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 734, \"to\": 740}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hepworth's bronze medal success comes just over an hour after finishing seventh in the men's rings final and he admitted the afternoon was a \\\"crazy\\\" experience.\", \"from\": 743, \"to\": 903, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 743, \"end\": 751, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resourc